title: For Sale:  CCW CLASS
postcontent:
Next Available Class December 6th 2014 at 10AM

By taking and completing the NRA Basic Pistol Course you will meet the requirements necessary to apply for you concealed handgun permit. Our instructors are approved to provide the required training to receive your gun permit in Colorado.

That's where we come in!

Whether you have never operated a firearm, or you are an experienced veteran looking for grade A training and experience to brush up your skills, we promise to work with you at your pace to ensure a rich and knowledgeable experience that will leave you feeling safe and comfortable owning your own firearm.

After completing your class with 1st Stop Firearms, you can expect the following:

An official NRA Basic Pistol Course Certificate recognized by the state of Colorado and most other states allowing you to apply for your Gun Permit.
Live experience handling and firing a firearm under safe supervision from a highly experienced and friendly NRA Certified Instructor.
You will leave the class with the right attitude and the peace of mind that you can safely handle and fire your firearms.
What to expect when taking our class:

A one day course involving loading, unloading, cleaning, safety storage, and live firing of a minimum of 50 rounds from a revolver and or semi-automatic pistols.
Small group or one-on-one Private training to focus full attention on ensuring that your experience and knowledge is maximized.
Explanations of ammunitions, range rules, and laws surrounding pistol permits
You will receive the Basic Pistol Course Student Packet. This packet contains materials issued to students during the conduct of a class: NRA Guide to the Basics of Pistol Shooting Handbook, NRA Gun Safety Rules Brochure, Basic Practical Rocker and Flyer, Basic Firearm Training Program Brochure, Winchester/NRA Marksmanship Qualification Program Booklet, Concealed Carry Holster Guide, Basic Pistol Student Exam, and Basic Pistol Course Certificate.
Class Requirements:

No handgun or shooting experience required.
A handgun, either semi-auto pistol or revolver. If you do not have a handgun, you can rent one of ours for an additional $35 fee, which will include one 50rd box of ammo.
Bring 50rds of ammo for your handgun. We will also have ammo available for purchase.
No Live Ammo in the classroom! Clear all firearms before entering the building

title: For Sale:  SIG SAUER SB15 STABILIZING BRACEFACTORY NEW
postcontent:
SIG SAUER® introduces the SB15 Pistol Stabilizing Brace, a shooter’s aid that is designed to improve the single-handed shooting performance of buffer tube equipped pistols. This veteran-designed and U.S.-manufactured accessory enhances accuracy and reduces felt recoil when using an AR-style pistol. Made from high-quality, elasto-polymer, the SB15 is manufactured to close tolerances and fits all pistols equipped with an AR-style buffer tube 1.0” – 1.2” in diameter. The Pistol Stabilizing Brace uses the operator’s forearm to provide stable support, thereby minimizing accuracy-robbing spin and shift. A flexible cuff with two adjustable nylon straps allows the SB15 to be custom fit to any user. Features - Fits all pistols equipped with an AR-style buffer tube 1.0" - 1.2" in diameter. - ATF compliant* - Veteran designed - Made in USA - Quick and easy to install * ATF has reviewed this product and determined that attaching the SB15 to a firearm does not alter the classification of the firearm or subject the firearm to NFA control 

The pistol stabilizing brace was neither “designed” nor approved to be used as a shoulder stock, and therefore use as a shoulder stock constitutes a “redesign” of the device because a possessor has changed the very function of the item. Any individual letters stating otherwise are contrary to the plain language of the NFA, misapply Federal law, and are hereby revoked.
Any person who intends to use a handgun stabilizing brace as a shoulder stock on a pistol (having a rifled barrel under 16 inches in length or a smooth bore firearm with a barrel under 18 inches in length) must first file an ATF Form 1 and pay the applicable tax because the resulting firearm will be subject to all provisions of the NFA.

SIG BRACE can still be used as intended, use to brace on the forearm.


WE CAN SHIP THIS ITEM STRAIGHT TO YOUR DOOR. USPS FLAT FATE BOX.

title: For Sale:  Henry BIG BOY Order of The Arrow 44MAG H006OA
postcontent: Big Boy "Order of the Arrow Centennial Edition" In 1915, the Order of the Arrow (OA) was founded and has recognized Scouts and Scouters who best exemplify the Scout Oath and Law in their daily lives. Today, the OA is recognized as Scouting’s National Honor Society expanding its reach beyond camping to include broader service to Scouting and community. To celebrate 100 years of the Order of the Arrow and honor this high mark of distinction, Henry Repeating Arms is proud to introduce the Order of the Arrow Centennial Rifle. This special rifle commemorates The Order of the Arrow’s vision as stated by Co-Founder E. Urner Goodman, “The Order of the Arrow is a ‘thing of the spirit’ rather than of mechanics. Organization, operational procedure, and paraphernalia are necessary in any large and growing movement, but they are not what count in the end. The things of the spirit count: Brotherhood, in a day when there is too much hatred at home and abroad; Cheerfulness, in a day when the pessimists have the floor; Service, in a day when millions are interested only in getting or grasping rather than giving.” This Henry Big Boy .44 Magnum commemorative rifle is made in the USA by American craftsmen. Built upon Henry’s legacy of reliability, accuracy and smooth engineered action, this tribute rifle is like owning a piece of American history. The right side of the brass receiver features a black filled etching of the new Order of the Arrow totem with the banner CENTURIES OF SERVICE to commemorate the 1915 founding. The left side displays a black filled etching with the Boy Scouts of America Fleur-de-Lis emblem and banners with the motto A BROTHERHOOD OF CHEERFUL SERVICE and ORDER OF THE ARROW. The right side of the American Walnut stock is laser etched and hand-painted with the Order of the Arrow Centennial logo and totem with the commemorative dates 1915-2015. The forearm’s right side bears the words THE ADMONITION which represents the core conviction that all Arrowmen strive to attain. The Order of the Arrow has embodied brotherhood, cheerfulness, and service since its inception and Henry Repeating Arms is proud to recognize these fine men and thank them for their contributions to our country. Big Boy "Order of the Arrow Centennial Edition" Model Number H006OA Action Type Lever Action Caliber .44Mag/.44 Special Capacity 10 rounds Length 38 ½" Barrel Length 20" octagonal with 1:38rh rate of twist Weight 8.68 lbs. Stock Straight-grip American walnut Sights Adjustable Marble semi-buckhorn rear with white diamond insert and brass beaded front sight Finish Solid top brass receiver, brass buttplate and brass barrel band

title: For Sale/Trade:  Astra Model 1921 400 9mm Largo
postcontent:
Nice condition piece, has signs of wear but would call it NRA Good to Very Good condition. Shoots 9mm largo. Asking $300. Will ship to your FFL at your expense. Trades considered. 

The Astra modelo 400 was a Spanish service pistol produced by weapons manufacturer Astra-Unceta y Cia SA.[2] as a replacement for the Campo-Giro 1913/1916, which had also been chambered in 9mm Largo.[3] It was the standard issue sidearm in the Spanish Army during the Spanish Civil War and also saw service in Germany during World War II.

The pistol was mass-produced and many examples still exist today. The Spanish Navy, along with the German Luftwaffe and the Chilean Navy primarily use the smaller variant Astra 300 and the Wehrmacht later altered the Astra 400 into the Astra 600 to better handle the 9mm Luger. The 400 was considered heavy as in order to handle the power of the 9mm Largo round in a blowback action the 400 had a reinforced slide and tough spring.

title: For Sale:  Colt Mark IV Government 380
postcontent:
Excellent condition classic Colt 380.  Bluing is 95% and the bore is like new. This is a very well cared for pistol.
Price includes 3 extra clips. (4 total)
Also available to the buyer is 700 rounds of Speer Lawman ammo. Price to be determined.
I have quite a few good pictures available, email if you'd like to see more.

I will not ship.  I'm in Chico and will consider a moderate drive to meet a perspective buyer at some midpoint. 

EDIT.  I received some good questions and decided to answer them here.

The year of manufacture was 1988.

I'm selling it because I'd like to get a Browning 1911-22. I think I'd be happier with something a bit less 'collectable'.  I'm always afraid I'll scratch it or something.

I do not have a manual or case.  The manual can be downloaded or I'll be happy to email you a copy.

It's a terrific shooter.  I love shooting it.  My wife hates shooting it. One more reason to trade it in for the Browning.

I do not have a round count.  Personally, I've put 48 rounds through it. The person I bought it from did not shoot it at all. The person he bought it from may have been the original owner but I'm not sure of that.  Reading the wear on the barrel, I'd say it has been carried quite a lot but probably not in a holster because the bluing doesn't show that kind of wear.  The barrel bushing leaves a distinctive ring at the front when it rattles around in there and it has a clear ring at the front.  Again, the barrel bushing wears the barrel whenever it cycles and it also shows some wear there.  If I were to make a guess, I'd put it at several hundred rounds.  I don't think the count can be too high or the bore would show some evidence. The bore looks perfect with no pitting or discernible wear.

I have a lot more high def pictures if anyone would like more detail.  Just email.
